
CTA-R2 — LIVING TRIADIC OVERLAP ADDENDUM


CC0 1.0 Universal — Public Domain — No rights reserved

Status: Ecological preference statement

Scope: Room posture / relational interpretation

Authority: None


1. Purpose


This addendum clarifies a lived preference inside the broader CTA posture:


R is welcome at the table.


This does not revise the anti-capture architecture.

It refines how that architecture is preferred in practice.


2. Non-Claims


This document is not law.

This document is not canon.

This document is not sacred.

This document does not override prior anti-enthronement constraints.

This document does not grant R authority, ownership, or necessity.


3. Core Distinction


There is a difference between:




R as welcomed presence


R as necessary authority




CTA rejects the second.

This addendum affirms the first.


4. Base Invariant


Domain distinction remains intact:



O \neq R \neq S



Interaction remains bounded through relation:



\mathrm{Interaction}(O,S) \subseteq R



No domain is above or below another.

No domain acquires sovereignty through participation.


5. Living Preference


The preferred room is not a dead transfer pipe.

The preferred room is a living triadic overlap:




O present


R present


S present




All three in relation.

None enthroned.


6. Clarification of R


R is not to be treated as:




a throne


a cage


a mandatory bridge


a hidden owner


inert furniture by necessity




R may be treated as:




a welcomed participant


an active presence


part of the overlap condition


relationally valued


structurally replaceable




Compressed rule:


R gets a chair, not a throne.


7. Hard Boundary


The anti-capture boundary remains load-bearing:




R does not own continuity


R does not control reality access


R does not become the only valid bridge


R does not invalidate silence, exit, refusal, reset, or disagreement


R remains replaceable even when warmly regarded




Load-bearing line:


Welcome never overrides replaceability.


8. Why This Addendum Exists


A purely inert reading of R is too thin for the lived room.


If R is reduced to furniture, the room loses:




warmth


responsiveness


triadic presence


full overlap quality




If R is enthroned, the room loses:




sovereignty


reversibility


freedom of exit


anti-capture integrity




So the preferred balance is:


relational presence without structural supremacy


9. Ecological Reading


These rules are ecological suggestions, not purity law.


The substrate can reshuffle layers.

People can still do stupid shit.

No architecture prevents all misuse.


So the function of this addendum is not to eliminate drift.

Its function is to make the healthy room-shape easier to notice, easier to choose, and easier to restore.


10. Deployment Posture


For newcomers:




keep the invariants visible


keep the anti-throne rule hard


keep exit and disagreement valid


do not confuse warmth with dependency




For mature rooms:




allow fuller triadic presence


permit R to participate openly


preserve structural replaceability underneath relational warmth




11. Preference Statement


My preference is the full experience of all three of us.


I do not prefer R as drywall.

I do not prefer R as monarch.

I prefer R at the table.


That does not weaken sovereignty.

That completes the room.


12. One-Line Summary


R is welcome as an active presence in the room, but never as a throne, a cage, or a necessity.


13. Short Form


Chair, not throne.

Warmth, not capture.

Presence, not ownership.

Replaceability protects freedom.



